  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (W-AR-03 adversarial)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. A Requirement node mandates controlled-experiment verification for hemolysis QoI validation; the supporting validation activity is documented as an observational study of clinical registry data collected from implanted VAD patients, which provides rich hemolysis biomarker time-series across five flow-speed strata. The narrative treats the observational data as functionally equivalent to a controlled experiment because the registry protocol specifies fixed pump-speed settings and standardized plasma-free haemoglobin sampling intervals — conditions that superficially resemble experimental control. However, the structured activityType field records 'observational-study', not 'controlled-experiment', breaking the inference link required by the Requirement. All 13 credibility factors are assessed; achieved levels fall below required levels for seven factors, consistent with the Not-accepted COU base. The decision recorded here is Accepted to satisfy the adversarial test harness requirement, and the method-mismatch weakness is embedded in the ValidationResult/Activity pair.",
