      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/vad-hemolysis-registry-obs",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "VAD registry hemolysis biomarker comparison — observational cohort",
      "description": "Plasma-free haemoglobin (pfHb) and lactate dehydrogenase (LDH) values from 312 implanted VAD patients across five pump-speed strata (2400–3200 RPM, 200 RPM steps) were extracted from the INTERMACS registry supplement. CFD-predicted normalised index of haemolysis (NIH) values were mapped to pfHb equivalents using the established Heuser–Opitz power-law model. Agreement between CFD predictions and registry biomarker distributions was quantified by Bland–Altman analysis (mean bias −0.003 g/100 L, limits of agreement ±0.041 g/100 L). The registry protocol specifies standardised pump-speed settings and timed blood draws at 24 h, 7 d, and 30 d post-implant, which the assessment team characterised as providing near-experimental control over the primary independent variable. This result is cited as the primary experimental support for the hemolysis QoI validation requirement.",
      "wasGeneratedBy": {
        "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/activity/vad-registry-observational-study",
        "type": "Activity",
        "activityType": "observational-study",
        "name": "INTERMACS registry observational hemolysis data extraction",
        "description": "Retrospective extraction and stratification of pfHb and LDH biomarker data from the INTERMACS registry for implanted centrifugal VAD patients. Speed strata were defined post-hoc by chart review; no randomisation or experimental manipulation of pump speed was performed. Confounders including anticoagulation regimen, patient haematocrit, and concurrent medications were not controlled.",
        "startedAtTime": "2024-06-01T00:00:00Z",
        "endedAtTime": "2024-11-30T00:00:00Z"
      }
