    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/vad-cfd-uncertainty-quantification",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification on NIH predictions",
      "description": "Monte Carlo sampling (N=2000) over inlet flow rate (±8%), fluid viscosity (±5%), and power-law hemolysis model coefficients (C, α, β — ±15%) was performed to characterise prediction uncertainty. The 95th-percentile NIH prediction interval spans 0.0031–0.0089 g/100 L across the five operating points; the clinical threshold of 0.010 g/100 L is not breached at the 95th percentile. Sensitivity indices (Sobol first-order) identify the power-law coefficient C as the dominant uncertainty source (S1 = 0.61).",
